<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ɡʲa</span></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ɡʲaʔəs</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>near-you visible</td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">us</span></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">q</span></td>
<td></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">uχ</span></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">(a)χs</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>near-you invisible</td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">us</span></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">qʼ</span></td>
<td></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">uχ</span></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">qʼəs</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>elsewhere visible</td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">is</span></td>
<td>--</td>
<td></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">i</span></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">s</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>elsewhere invisible</td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">is</span></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">a</span></td>
<td></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">i</span></td>
<td>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">as</span></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Prenominal forms for the objective and instrumental are formed by suffixing the prenominal forms given above to <i>-<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">χ</span></i> or <i><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">s</span></i> respectively.</p>
<p>Independent pronouns also exist in Kwak'wala. Pronouns have verbal and nominal forms. Verbal forms inflect like other verbs. Nominal forms occur in subject, object and instrumental forms. The full set of pronouns is shown in the following table:</p>
<table class="wikitable">
